Address: Hills and Dales MetroPark, S Patterson Blvd, Kettering, OH 45419, United States

Name: Perry's Cave Family Fun Center
Description: Family-fun complex with a limestone cave, mini golf, gem mining, a rock wall & a butterfly house.
Address: 979 Catawba Ave, Put-In-Bay, OH 43456, United States

Name: Merry-Go-Round Museum
Description: Museum featuring a working, vintage carousel, a collection of antique, carved animals & a gift shop.
Address: 301 Jackson St, Sandusky, OH 44870, United States

Name: Ghostly Manor Thrill Center
Description: Family-friendly entertainment center with a haunted house, mini-golf, a 3D theater & a skating rink.
Address: 3319 Milan Rd, Sandusky, OH 44870, United States

Name: Watch House & Circle Mound
Description: An unusual spherical observatory sits on the highest point of a 200-foot diameter earth mound in Dublin, Ohio.
Address: 5200 Emerald Pkwy, Dublin, OH 43017, United States

Name: Squire's Castle
Description: A 19th-century castle-style home within North Chagrin Reservation, surrounded by scenic landscapes.
Address: 2844 River Rd, Willoughby Hills, OH 44094, United States

Name: Quilted Rock
Description: A tall boulder painted in bright-colored squares in an otherwise flat, green landscape.
Address: 6622-6748 Karch Rd, Celina, OH 45822, United States

Name: Castle Noel
Description: America's Largest Indoor Christmas Entertainment Attraction. See part of Hollywood & NYC in Medina. Breathtaking displays. Surprises!
Address: 260 S Court St, Medina, OH 44256, United States

Name: Alien Vacation Mini Golf Attraction at Castle Noel
Description: Alien-themed, black-lit 18-hole indoor mini-golf course, with animated features & 3D effects.
Address: 260 S Court St, Medina, OH 44256, United States

Name: The Ohio State Reformatory
Description: Built in 1886, this Romanesque Revival prison was featured in the film "The Shawshank Redemption."
Address: 100 Reformatory Rd, Mansfield, OH 44905, United States

Name: Fort Ancient
Description: Landmark parkland featuring trails & a museum on American Indian heritage & early European settlers.

Name: The BIG Rocking Chair
Description: Not the largest, but still an impressive 20 feet tall. Now owned by an adjacent hospice, advertised with a banner on the chair.

Name: Giant Amish Horse and Buggy
Description: The wooden horse and buggy are perfectly proportional to an actual horse and buggy, and uses 2300 board feet of lumber.

Name: Glacial Grooves
Description: Limestone bedrock with fossils & deep grooves caused by glacial activity around 18,000 years ago.
Address: 739 Division St, Kelleys Island, OH 43438, United States

Name: SunWatch Indian Village
Description: Excavated remains of a 13th-century Native American village, with exhibits & artifacts.
Address: 2301 W River Rd, Dayton, OH 45417, United States

Name: Biblewalk
Description: Waxwork museum with around 300 biblical figures, rare bibles, art & wood carvings, with tours.
Address: 500 Tingley Ave, Mansfield, OH 44905, United States

Name: USS Cod Submarine Memorial
Description: Open for tours from May 1 to September 30, this World War II-era sub honors fallen submariners.
Address: 1201 N Marginal Rd, Cleveland, OH 44114, United States

Name: Old Train Bridge
Address: 980 Caywood Rd, Marietta, OH 45750, United States

Name: Emeraldgate Skeletons
Address: 8908 Emeraldgate Dr, Huber Heights, OH 45424, United States

Name: Buckland Museum of Witchcraft & Magick
Description: Museum of items collected by Raymond Buckland who started collecting in 1966.
Address: 2155 Broadview Rd, Cleveland, OH 44109, United States

Name: North Chagrin Reservation
Description: Wildlife-rich area with woodland & wetland trails to Buttermilk Falls Preserve & Squire's Castle.
Address: 3037 SOM Ctr Rd, Willoughby Hills, OH 44094, United States

Name: America's Packard Museum
Description: Large collection of preserved cars, motorcycles & artifacts in an original Packard dealership.
Address: 420 S Ludlow St, Dayton, OH 45402, United States

Name: Leo Petroglyphs
Description: The petroglyph is located near the small village of Leo, Ohio and is thought to have been created by the Fort Ancient peoples.
Address: 400 Park Rd, Ray, OH 45672, United States

Name: Arnold Statue
Description: The statue of Arnold Schwarzenegger is an 8-foot-tall, 800 lb bronze sculpture of bodybuilding legend Arnold Schwarzenegger performing his signature 'twisted double biceps pose'. It is installed in Columbus, Ohio, United States
Address: 486 N High St #474, Columbus, OH 43215, United States

Name: Hayden Falls Park
Description: Park featuring a 35-ft. waterfall & an overlook accessed via a boardwalk, plus picnic tables.
Address: 4326 Hayden Run Rd, Dublin, OH 43017, United States

Name: Statue of Liberty Replica
Description: A 7-foot, 7-inch aluminum replica of the Statue of Liberty that stands in Old Church Park at the corner of Cherry and Morning Streets in Sunbury, Ohio.
Address: 1 N Center St, Newton Falls, OH 44444, United States

Name: Trammel Fossil Park
Description: This park is very unique and includes fossils originating from the Ordovician Period, dating over 440 million years ago.
Address: 11935 Tramway Dr, Sharonville, OH 45241, United States

Name: William McKinley Memorial
Description: Landmark domed mausoleum on a hill, resting place of William McKinley, 25th American president.
Address: 800 Mc Kinley Monument Dr NW, Canton, OH 44708, United States

Name: Olentangy Caverns | Rock & Gem Gift Shop
Description: The local Delaware tribe used to inhabit these caverns, now accessible for tours in season only.
Address: 1779 Home Rd, Delaware, OH 43015, United States

Name: Former Pennsylvania Railroad Middletown JCT
Address: 1098 River Forest Dr, Maineville, OH 45039, United States

Name: The Ted Lewis Museum
Description: Celebrating the life and preserving the legacy of Circleville's own Ted Lewis!
Address: 133 W Main St, Circleville, OH 43113, United States

Name: Giant "LOT BALL"
Description: Big polystyrene orb officially titled both "Lot Ball" and "Perpetual Motion" covered with asphalt and painted with parking lot lines and directional arrows. Artist Lars Fisk says he was inspired by his local Costco parking lot
Address: 7001 Carnegie Ave, Cleveland, OH 44103, United States

Name: Garst Museum
Description: The Garst House, also known as the Garst Museum, is an historic building located at 205 North Broadway in Greenville, Ohio, United States.
Address: 205 N Broadway St, Greenville, OH 45331, United States

Name: International Women’s Air & Space Museum
Description: This museum in the Burke Lakefront Airport chronicles the history of women in aviation & space.
Address: 1501 N Marginal Rd, Cleveland, OH 44114, United States

Name: Armstrong Air & Space Museum
Description: Orb-shaped space museum featuring interactive displays on lunar excursions & Neil Armstrong.
Address: 500 Apollo Dr, Wapakoneta, OH 45895, United States

Name: Spirit of 76 Museum
Description: The Spirit of ‘76 Museum is located in downtown Wellington, Ohio. The museum is dedicated to the memory of Archibald M. Willard, the artist who created the “Spirit of ‘76,” America’s most inspirational patriotic painting.
Address: 201 N Main St, Wellington, OH 44090, United States

Name: Willard Park
Description: Iconic home to the large outdoor sculpture "Free Stamp" by Claes Oldenburg & Coosje van Bruggen.
Address: Lakeside Avenue East &, E 9th St, Cleveland, OH, United States

Name: Indian Head Rock
Description: The Indian Head Rock is an eight-ton sandstone boulder, which had rested at the bottom of the Ohio River, until September 2007 when it was retrieved by a group of local divers, led by amateur historian Steve Shaffer of Ironton, Ohio.

Name: The Feline Historical Museum
Address: 260 E Main St, Alliance, OH 44601, United States

Name: A-MAZE-N FUNHOUSE
Description: Our A-Maze-N Funhouse, designed like an old-time circus midway, is sure to be an adventure for the whole family!
Address: 7379 Squire Ct, West Chester Township, OH 45069, United States

Name: Hippo Statue
Description: Home-built hippo stands beside the road, with an open mouth and weird, blood red zombie eyes.
Address: 615-631 Dayton Springfield Rd, Springfield, OH 45506, United States

Name: DublinSpring
Address: 20 S Riverview St, Dublin, OH 43017, United States

Name: Wood County Museum
Description: This structure was the home to poor, mentally- ill, physically disabled and anyone in need of public assistance who were residents of Wood County.
Address: 13660 County Home Rd, Bowling Green, OH 43402, United States

Name: OHIO Sculpture
Address: 100 Park Ave, Beachwood, OH 44122, United States

Name: Ohio River Scenic Pull Off
Address: Ohio River Scenic Byway, Marietta, OH 45750, United States

Name: World's Largest Basket by Longaberger
Description: The World's Largest Apple Basket over 29 feet tall stands at the original Longaberger Homestead in Frazeysburg.
Address: E 5th St &, Main St, Dresden, OH 43821, United States

Name: The Haserot Angel
Description: Cleveland's Lakeview Cemetery contains over 100,000 graves, including those of presidents and business moguls. However, its most striking grave marker may be the unsettling statue known as Haserot's Angel.
Address: 12316 Euclid Ave, Cleveland, OH 44106, United States

Name: Snook's Dream Cars
Description: Automobile history comes alive in Snook’s Dream Cars Automobile Museum fittingly located adjacent to one of America’s first cross- country highways, U.S. Route 6, in Bowling Green, Ohio.
Address: 13920 County Home Rd, Bowling Green, OH 43402, United States

Name: Greetings From Toledo
Address: 120 Main St, Toledo, OH 43605, United States

Name: Flight of the Hawk Park
Description: It is composed of more than 3,000 torch-cut pieces that were artfully shaped and welded into place by local artist, Ric Leichliter.  It weighs an impressive 2,500 pounds!
Address: 4750 Old Logan Rd SE, Lancaster, OH 43130, United States

Name: Wyandot Popcorn Museum
Description: The Old U.S. Post Office in Marion, Ohio was built in 1910. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1990.
Address: 169 E Church St, Marion, OH 43302, United States

Name: Morgan County Dungeon
Description: The Morgan County Dungeon was discovered in 1964 during excavation for the present sheriff's office and jail. Located beneath the basement in the old jail, the dungeon contained several artifacts and is a stark reminder of how criminals were dealt with in the 19th century.

Name: Berea Falls Scenic Overlook- Barret Overlook
Description: Berea Falls is a double tiered cascade on the West Fork of the Rocky River and is located at the southern reaches of the 2,572-acre Rocky River Reservation.
Address: 136 E Bagley Rd, Berea, OH 44017, United States

Name: Ohio Welcome Sign
Address: 888 S Irvine Ave, Masury, OH 44438, United States

Name: Welcome to Ohio Sign
Address: North Beaver Township, PA 16120, United States

Name: Welcome To Ohio Sign
Address: 7989 Cincinnati Brookville Rd, Okeana, OH 45053, United States

Name: Welcome to Ohio Sign
Address: State Line Rd, Jackson Township, IN 45880, United States

Name: Welcome to Ohio Sign
Address: 325 Main St, Bridgeport, OH 43912, United States

Name: Welcome sign OHIO
Address: US-52, Coal Grove, OH 45638, United States

Name: Blue Whale of Catoosa
Description: Large Route 66 roadside whale, built in 1972 on a small pond with a nearby picnicking area.

Name: Ed Galloway's Totem Pole Park
Description: Completed in 1961, this folk-art park features elaborate carved totems created by Ed Galloway.
Address: 21300 OK-28 A, Chelsea, OK 74016, United States

Name: OK County 66 - John's Place
Description: Quirky local art gallery celebrating Route 66 with cars, memorabilia & vintage signs.

Name: National Cowboy & Western Heritage Museum
Description: Dioramas, artifacts, art & more documenting & interpreting the history of the American West.
Address: 1700 NE 63rd St, Oklahoma City, OK 73111, United States

Name: Charley Border
Description: Originally called the Lil Jim, the Charley Border is now a museum exhibit in front of the Oklahoma Maritime Educational Center. The engine room and floor plates of the towboat were galvanized with a tonnage of 1,500 lbs.
Address: 5350 Main Pkwy, Catoosa, OK 74015, United States

Name: Painted Horse "Oklahoma Scissortail"
Description: One of the painted horses that are scattered across Shawnee, Oklahoma

Name: Museum of Osteology
Description: Unique spot for educational exhibits of 300+ skeletons of many species plus hands-on displays.
Address: 10301 S Sunnylane Rd, Oklahoma City, OK 73160, United States

Name: The Toy & Action Figure Museum
Description: With the help of local artist and toy designer (and collector) Kevin Stark, a board was formed to start working on the world’ s first museum devoted to the art and sculpting of action figures!
Address: 111 S Chickasaw St, Pauls Valley, OK 73075, United States

Name: Model T Graveyard
Address: 4413 S Post Rd, Oklahoma City, OK 73150, United States

Name: Golden Driller Statue
Description: Iconic, 75-ft. statue of an oil driller with his hand resting on an oil derrick.
Address: Tulsa Expo Center, 4145 E 21st St, Tulsa, OK 74114, United States

Name: Spider Bug
Address: 951 Moffatt Rd, Lexington, OK 73051, United States

Name: Frog Rock
Description: This huge rock formation found in Terlton is well over six feet tall and is painted green and white to look like a friendly amphibian.
Address: Frog Rd, Terlton, OK 74081, United States

Name: Oklahoma Route 66 Museum
Description: A look at the history, myths, signs, photos & music of the iconic road, plus a diner replica.
Address: 2229 W Gary Blvd, Clinton, OK 73601, United States

Name: Salt Plains State Park
Description: Hiking & digging for crystals in a landscape of salt flats, plus lake fishing, a beach & campsite
Address: 23280 S Spillway Dr, Jet, OK 73749, United States

Name: Sandhill Curiosity Shop
Description: The Sandhills Curiosity Shop, known as the oldest brick building in Erick, can accommodate up to 75 people.
Address: 201 S Sheb Wooley Ave, Erick, OK 73645, United States

Name: Centennial Land Run Monument
Description: Huge bronze statue marking the opening of the land in Oklahoma Territory with the Land Run of 1889.
Address: 200 Centennial Ave, Oklahoma City, OK 73102, United States

Name: Blue Hippo
Description: Bud Fisher’s knowledge of the hippo, whom he calls Happy Hippo, goes back 30 years.
Address: 1129 S Broadway, Edmond, OK 73034, United States

Name: OkieTundra
Address: U.S. Rt. 66, Tulsa, OK 73059, United States

Name: Stone Horse
Address: 1201 N Mustang Rd, Mustang, OK 73064, United States

Name: Arcadia Round Barn
Description: A round, red 1898 barn, now a historic roadside attraction & popular Route 66 pit stop.

Name: Oklahoma City National Memorial & Museum
Description: A garden, pool & sculptural memorial commemorating victims of the 1995 Murrah Building bombing.
Address: 620 N Harvey Ave, Oklahoma City, OK 73102, United States

Name: Woolaroc Museum & Wildlife Preserve
Description: Sprawling wildlife preserve with a rustic lodge & a museum dedicated to Southwest art & relics.
Address: 1925 Woolaroc Ranch Rd, Barnsdall, OK 74002, United States

Name: Seaba Station Motorcycle Museum
Description: The Seaba Station was built in 1921, five years before historic Route 66 was certified as a national highway.
Address: 336992 East, OK-66, Warwick, OK 74881, United States

Name: D W Correll Museum
Description: The vehicles include an 1898 Locomobile, 1906 Cadillac, 1915 Dodge touring car, 1914 Oldsmobile, 1917 Twin 6 Packard and more. All are in working condition.
Address: 19934 E Pine St, Catoosa, OK 74015, United States

Name: Shattuck Windmill Museum
Description: 37 windmills stand in the park, with no two alike, from a little 5 foot "Star Zephyr" to the big 18 foot "Samson." Some are solid wooden wheels, others have wooden wheels that fold and many are unusual steel mills
Address: 1201-1299 Main St, Shattuck, OK 73858, United States

Name: Simpson's Old Time Museum
Description: Wagons, saddles, dolls & Western film sets at an eclectic museum with an on-site production company.
Address: 228 E Randolph Ave, Enid, OK 73701, United States

Name: Route 66 Robot by Sawyer Fab at OKC Tower Theatre
Description: Rt-19 is part of the “Robots on 66” series, a creative project that adds fun robot statues to popular destinations along Oklahoma’s stretch of Route 66.
Address: 432 NW 23rd St, Oklahoma City, OK 73103, United States

Name: Stafford Air & Space Museum
Description: Popular indoor/outdoor museum featuring over 3,500 aerospace artifact & interactive activities.
Address: 3000 Logan Rd, Weatherford, OK 73096, United States

Name: Lucille's Historic Highway Gas Station
Description: The Provine Service Station is a historic filling station on U.S. Route 66 in Oklahoma. Located a half-mile south of Hydro, Oklahoma and operated by Lucille Hamons from 1941 until her death on August 18, 2000
Address: U.S. Rt. 66, Hydro, OK 73048, United States

Name: Sequoyah's Cabin Museum
Description: It was the home between 1829 and 1844 of the Cherokee Indian Sequoyah, who in 1821 created a written language for the Cherokee Nation.

Name: The American Pigeon Museum & Library
Description: Modern museum dedicated to the history & heritage of domestic pigeons, with exhibits & live birds.
Address: 2300 NE 63rd St, Oklahoma City, OK 73111, United States

Name: Oklahoma National Guard Museum
Description: State-run, free-entry indoor/outdoor museum displaying military history artifacts & memorabilia.
Address: 2145 NE 36th St, Oklahoma City, OK 73111, United States

Name: American Banjo Museum
Description: Exhibits on the history of the banjo with hundreds on display, plus memorabilia, recordings & more.
Address: 9 E Sheridan Ave, Oklahoma City, OK 73104, United States

Name: The Cave House
Address: 1623 Charles Page Blvd, Tulsa, OK 74127, United States

Name: Crosstar Flag and Tag
Description: Opened in 2022 by Al Childs in his back yard, which faces Route 66. There's a robot, a mini-Space Shuttle, odd vehicles and art. Al accumulated over 6,000 license plates.
Address: 103 S Central Ave, Afton, OK 74331, United States

Name: The Holy City of the Wichitas
Description: Just outside of Lawton in the beautiful Wichita Mountains Wildlife Refuge sits the Holy City of the Wichitas, a 66-acre replica of ancient Jerusalem and North America's longest continuously running Easter pageant.
Address: 262 Holy City Rd, Lawton, OK 73507, United States

Name: Three Rivers Museum
Description: Museum dedicated to local history, with rotating food trucks in the parking lot every Thursday.
Address: 220 Elgin St, Muskogee, OK 74401, United States

Name: Heart of Route 66 Auto Museum
Description: Heart of Route 66 Auto Museum began as the dream of Richard Holmes, a Tulsa attorney and car enthusiast.
Address: 13 Sahoma Lake Rd, Sapulpa, OK 74066, United States
